Avatars let you express something about yourself. By integrating info from the blockchain (collection, creators‚Ä¶), it turns out NFTs can be much more expressive than JPEGs :)

Broadly, this is a step towards building a better Twitter by integrating with decentralized networks. https://t.co/7N7FRLsS1y

The growing crypto and NFT communities on Twitter have looked for solutions to NFT ownership verification, so a lot of thought went into the hex, which signals ownership at a glance. You can then tap the pfp to see information about its collection and chain. https://t.co/YwYwrnJcgU

NFT pfps are an upgrade to good ol' JPEGs. Their hex shape signals ownership and they have contextual info from the blockchain - name, collection, description, creators...

To start, sign a message w/ your ETH wallet to verify NFT ownership. Learn more: https://t.co/NybrbwJt9h
